abstract: At the end of her sophomore year in college, Mary Beth Keane’s writing teacher gave her a summer reading list that changed her life.
snippet: At the end of her sophomore year in college, Mary Beth Keane’s writing teacher gave her a summer reading list that changed her life.
lead_paragraph: When I was a kid in the late 1980s, the reading material in my house consisted of: our local newspaper, an Irish newspaper and Reader’s Digest, which came only once a month. My favorite section in Reader’s Digest was called “Drama in Real Life” and featured a true story about a life-threatening experience. Once, a babysitter asked me where my younger sisters’ bedtime books were kept. I told her there weren’t any books, but she could try reading “Drama in Real Life” to them if she wanted. On that occasion, the story was about a man who was cutting down trees on his property and somehow touched his chain saw to a steel wire. The saw got stripped of its blades and tore him up like shrapnel. I don’t remember how he survived, but I do remember that my sisters were riveted. What power, I thought, to be able to bring people to the edge of their seats, impatient to know what would happen next.

abstract: Mr. Epstein, charged with sex trafficking, cultivated an intimate, yearslong relationship with Leslie Wexner — and proceeded to get extraordinarily rich.
snippet: Mr. Epstein, charged with sex trafficking, cultivated an intimate, yearslong relationship with Leslie Wexner — and proceeded to get extraordinarily rich.
lead_paragraph: In May 1997, Alicia Arden, a model in California, was introduced to a man who identified himself as a talent scout for Victoria’s Secret. He invited her to his Santa Monica hotel room to audition for the brand’s catalog. When she arrived, Ms. Arden said, the man grabbed her, tried to undress her and said he wanted to “manhandle” her. Ms. Arden, then 27, fled in tears.

abstract: A would-be novelist roams Barcelona as a chauffeur who is the captive of his own overactive imagination in this film by Jorge M. Fontana.
snippet: A would-be novelist roams Barcelona as a chauffeur who is the captive of his own overactive imagination in this film by Jorge M. Fontana.
lead_paragraph: No, not Dat Boi. This one: Boi Salt, of Barcelona, the title character in the Spanish-language import “Boi,” from Netflix. Poor guy, to be saddled with a name so freighted with stale internet meme baggage. And that’s the least of his worries.

lead_paragraph: JAY ELECTRONICA at 99 Scott (July 28, 6 p.m.). One of hip-hop’s most elusive personalities, this rapper has spent more than a decade dodging fans’ eager pleas for a proper debut album. In 2007, he released his breakout project, “Act 1: Eternal Sunshine (The Pledge),” an experimental collage piece built on the soundtrack to “Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind.” Since then he has dropped just a handful of his own singles, and taken guest turns on tracks by Chance the Rapper, Mac Miller and others. Despite his resistance to the brisk pace of contemporary rap, Electronica’s much-lauded lyricism and ruminations on spirituality and struggle continue to captivate. mean.red

abstract: The most direct confrontation of the campaign yet is unfolding as candidates battle for the support of black voters and the next debate rapidly approaches.
snippet: The most direct confrontation of the campaign yet is unfolding as candidates battle for the support of black voters and the next debate rapidly approaches.
lead_paragraph: Joseph R. Biden Jr. entered the 2020 presidential campaign with wide support from black voters and a reservoir of good will stemming from his eight years as an unswervingly loyal vice president to Barack Obama — a huge head start in a primary where African-Americans will play a decisive role.

abstract: The musical based on the grandiose Meat Loaf album shines a light on its songwriter, Jim Steinman, and the many twists and turns it took to get both projects made.
snippet: The musical based on the grandiose Meat Loaf album shines a light on its songwriter, Jim Steinman, and the many twists and turns it took to get both projects made.
lead_paragraph: In the four decades since it was released, bearing the cover image of a motorcyclist blasting out of a graveyard on his bike, the Meat Loaf album “Bat Out Of Hell” has been described in many ways. Bombastic. Extravagant. Over-the-top.
